				<td colspan="2"><span>I am creating a Bard, I have decided on woodelf and will not change that decision, I would lite to be able to kite things, swarm kite, melee things ..., What should I put all my points into STA, or some into INT for mana pool or some into CHA for mob controll, or... What should I put my points into I have herd from the majority of High level bards that they all wish they had more hit points and had put their starting 25 into STA, Some also say they wish they had more INT, STR seems to be an easy stats to raise and im wondering if i should not use any beggining points on it? and Charisma is also relitvly easy to raise as int can be but at the expense of other stats, I would like to have a fair amount of HP's and be able to hand mob controll and have a decent mana pool.  The other problem I have is deciding on deity, Im hearing rallos Zek for armor, or Veeshanfor armor, or tunare for armor, or agnostic for illusion masks.
<br />
The Beggining WoodElf Bard stats are as follows: Theycan be basically every Deity.
<br />

<br />
RACE      STR  STA AGI DEX WIS INT CHA   BONUS 
<br />
Wood Elf  70    65   95   90   80  75   85       25  
<br />

<br />
Could as many people as possible please reccomend the areas to spend ____ amount of points and the deity, thank you.</span></td>
