				<td colspan="2"><span>Uhm.. Well, if you're going to melee, I'd say raise yer STA some, definitely, and STR.. I wouldn't worry too much about int, as you said, its not difficult to gather gear to raise it.. The thing I find myself missing the most on my bard (human) is strength.. But I'm only in my mid-40's yet.. *L* ..Other people would know better what serves best later in the game..
<br />

<br />
As for diety.. My bards all follow Tunare, and it hasn't caused me too much trouble.. There is just a TON of armor out there that is not diety-specific, and will give nice AC, stats, whatever your pleasure is.. You shouldn't have a problem gearing yourself no matter which diety you choose, or if you choose to be agnostic..</span></td>
