				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Creation<a name="5658"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 24 03 2:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yikes, I chose half-elf and now I see why... those are not great starting stats for a bard.  That being said you are set in your decision so here is what I would put your 25 pts into if I were you:
<br />

<br />
15 STA - My HPs suck at 56 (1675 with decent HP gear), you can never have enough HPs if you swarm due to mistakes/lag and meleeing, a simple reposit in PoD is 350 damage to me sometimes.
<br />

<br />
10 Str - This is a toss up. Your 70 str isn't very good so it could use some help, but str gear isn't THAT hard to come by so you may want to a few points into int. My int is only 105 and my manapool is decent but nothing to write home about.  Dex and cha are easy to increase but I put points into dex as I felt it lacking, 90 isn't bad to start.
<br />

<br />
You wouldn't go too far wrong with 20 into sta if you wanted but I like a bit more well rounded approach.
<br />

<br />
Diety? I went agnostic as mobs can see religion though illusions. My armor is non-diety specific cultural, I wouldn't have wanted the diety specific version.  My view is there is always gear out there for us agnostics, but if Rallos Zek is that uber and you can see yourself getting it then go for it.  I haven't used the illusions I have more than a handful of times and most of those times it was for conveineince rather than necessity.
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
