				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Creation<a name="5660"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 24 03 3:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'd put a bundle into STA and the rest into STR.
<br />

<br />
INT wont help you till 39 .. so you have time to get some +int gear and/or FT gear  - Im human bard with int of close to 75, I dont have a problem running out of mana I'm Level 55 .. with FT 1
<br />

<br />

<br />
CHA -- there is some debate as to how much a high CHA really helps .. again, wont really come into play 'till you are either swarm kiting or responsible for your group's CC  a CHA of 85 should not be too hard to push over 100 with items.
<br />

<br />
WIS -  Doesn't help bards
<br />

<br />
Dex - Helps with Fizzle and skill ups  90 is fair.  I boosted mine on purpose .. cuz I like weapons that proc<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
AGI - Helps with avoiding being hit during melee  95 is pretty good for a newbie bard
<br />

<br />
STA - Hit Points, Hit Points, Hit Points -- not to mention that if you have a STA of over 100, you suposedly dont suffer during combat when your STA bar drops to zero.  I see this as the only stat that will help a newbie bard right out of the chute ... by giving her more HPs.
<br />

<br />
STR - Lets you carry stuff .. and  I *think* it increases your damage during melee.  70 is low, and with the plate armor we can wear I wonder if you will become easily encoumbered. 
<br />

<br />
I'm agnostic, and have not noticed where that has been a problem for me.
<br />

<br />
That said....  I'd do something close to what Sin suggested.
<br />

<br />
Good luck<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
