			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Creation<a name="5664"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 24 03 3:52 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>cha - helps with fizzle, helps with lull, helps to get full damage,
<br />
        helps to get full duration of snare/slows/fear/charms.
<br />

<br />
dex - procs, dual weild, H-Attack, singing-through-battle,
<br />
        longest song duration (buffs).
<br />

<br />
agi - parry, dodge, damage mitigation, damage stability, AC,
<br />
       runspeed (only on extremes).
<br />

<br />
str - will increase max melee damage as well as ATK, will
<br />
       let you carry more stuff.
<br />

<br />
int - governs mana. skill increases.
<br />

<br />
wis - only helps for skill increases if you make it higher than
<br />
        your int, otherwise useless.
<br />

<br />
sta - hit points, AC.  At 101 sta you get the combat bonus 
<br />
       (or actually negate the drawback), increases underwater
<br />
       breathing time.
<br />

<br />
As a newbie bard you should melee as much as possible and
<br />
learn all of the weapon types that you are allowed to weild.
<br />

<br />
You can never have enough hp.
<br />

<br />
Charisma gear is difficult to get in the mid-levels, but high-end
<br />
items tend to have good bonuses so shouldn't be too much of
<br />
a worry.
<br />

<br />
If you have the gear ready for it the best long term investment
<br />
would be to put all the points in intelligence, the rest of the
<br />
stats won't be that difficult to increase whereas every single
<br />
bit of mana will help for Fading Memories.
<br />

<br />
some thoughts,
<br />

<br />
Astuce Subterfuge
<br />
